AUC/MPA+TAC were not done!                                                                           Adverse Events Visit 7:                                                                                       Adverse Event 1: Recurrent pyelonephritis of the transplant kidney caused by Pseudomonas aeruginosa (see Hospitalization 1!). For this, empiric intravenous antibiotics with Meropenem+Teicoplanin in combination were started (20.04.2022-21.04.2022), which was continued with only Meropenem for 4 days after confirmed findings (22.04.2022-25.04.2022) (see Antibiotics!). In the case of increasing poor renal function, combined intravenous antibiotics with Ceftazidim+Ciprofloxacin were administered at a dosage adapted to renal function (26.04.2022-06.05.2022) (see Antibiotics!)! On the discharge day (Hospitalization 1), intravenous antibiotics with Ciprofloxacin were switched to oral intake (07.05.2022-22.05.2022). Furthermore, it was decided not to give another Pentacarinate inhalation (Stop: 12.04.2022), but instead to use Cotrimoxazole (Content of 60 mg TMP) as PCP prophylaxis again (Start: 07.05.2022) (see Antibiotics)!                                                               Adverse Event 2: Recurrent gastroenteritis with detection of Norovirus and Clostridium difficile in stool (see Hospitaization 1!). Therefore antibiotic therapy with Vancomycin (22.04.2022-13.05.2022) (see Antibiotics) and antimycotic therapy with Nystatin (22.04.2022-22.05.2022) (see Antimycotics) were given!                           Adverse Event 3: New onset hypertension on 13.07.2022 is treated intermittently with Amlodipin (see Co-Medication)!                                                                     Adverse Event 4: Due to a Recurrence of Severe Neutropenia on 19.05.2022 (Neutrophils absolute: 0.330/nl), PCP prophylaxis with Cotrimoxazole (Stop: 19.05.2022) was discontinued again and replaced by further Pentacarinate inhalations (Restart: 22.05.2022, ongoing) (see Antibiotics)! In addition, Immunosuppression with Mycophenolate Mofetil 500 mg/d was interrupted until further notice (Stop: 19.05.2022)!                                                                                                    Adverse Event 5: A renal function scintigraphy of the transplant kidney on 27.04.2022 showed the Persistence of the urodynamically relevant Urinary transport disorder °II, more prominent than in the previous examination (see Visit 6), which was not least the reason for the degradation of renal function (see Hospitalization 1)! Adverse Event 6: A positive PCR test on 01.06.2022 revealed a SARS Cov 2 infection with mild cough as symptomatic (01.06.2022-05.07.2022)! Therefore antibiotic therapy with Ciprofloxacin was restarted on 07.06.2022 and was also continued due to persistent Neutropenia (Neutrophils absolute on 13.07.2022: 1,22 /nl), ongoing (see Antibiotics)!                                                                                               Adverse Event 7: On 06.07.2022 first recognizable Glucosuria, progressive in the course!                                                                                                            Visit 7: In case of relevant stenosis of the Transplant anastomosis with Acute functional degeneration of the transplant kidney (creatinine increase from 0.8 mg/dl to 3.7 mg/dl), a Ureteral reimplantation was performed on 28.04.2022. Thereupon recovery of the kidney graft function. In the course of this surgery an intravenous anesthesia was performed with Midazolam, Ropivacain, Sevofluran, Propofol, Sufentanil, Remifentanil, Cisatracurium, Antiemetics, NSAR and Corticosteroids were given!
